# cc-task audio-audit-O3b-usb-bandwidth-preflight-udev-hook (Auditor A O3b).
#
# When the Solid State Logic L-12 enumerates on a saturated xhci HC, the
# 12-channel UAC2 endpoint silently drops to 8 channels (or fails). Run a
# bandwidth preflight at the udev `add` event so the saturated-controller
# condition is caught before PipeWire's ALSA scan locks in the fallback.
#
# Ordered ahead of PipeWire's session-manager rules (default range 90+) so
# the preflight's textfile metric + ntfy alert land before downstream
# consumers see the device.
#
# Match: SSL L-12 USB MIDI/Audio composite device.
#   idVendor=0a4a (Solid State Logic)
#   idProduct=12c0 (L-12) — verify on operator's device with `lsusb`
#
# Install: operator install script symlinks the preflight script to
# /usr/local/bin/hapax-usb-bandwidth-preflight (the path udev sees,
# since udev rules run as root and don't see operator $HOME). This rule
# uses that stable absolute path; the symlink target lives in the
# repo at scripts/usb-bandwidth-preflight.sh.

ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTR{idVendor}=="0a4a", ATTR{idProduct}=="12c0", \
  RUN+="/usr/local/bin/hapax-usb-bandwidth-preflight --device-name 'Solid State Logic L-12'"
